	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Great Hierophant wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Your idea involves rewritting input routines in these games and using something like a SNES-NES adapter on the 2nd controller.  <br /><br />What about the other alternative, build an adapter that converts the mouse movement to control pad directions?</div><br />That would limit movement to the speeds and directions available through the Control Pad, and the uC in the middle would have to model the game's own acceleration or autorepeat in order to translate distances accurately.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Don't forget Shadowgate, Deja Vu, Uninvited, Linus Spearhead's Cosmic Crusade &amp; King's Quest V as games that would be improved with mouse support.</div><br />I left out Linus Spacehead's Cosmic Crusade because it's a Codemasters game, and Codemasters games are more likely to need the circuit to smooth double-clocks.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I think that adding a crosshair to Zapper games may prove difficult on the NES.</div><br />That depends on how hard it is to patch in a call to fill sprite 63.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I don't think that the gaming experience would improve with Zelda or Rad Racer, the first has control that is a tad loose</div><br />I imagined that the game would be patched such that the character would walk toward the cursor, much as in Diablo or the DS or Wii versions of Animal Crossing.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> and for the latter, they seldom benefit without something like a wheel.</div><br />8-bit racing games don't generally have the car actually turn. Instead, the game handles like a shooter: press left and the car turns left; let go of left and the car turns right to go straight. That brings up another point: a mouse patch would help Star Force.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Sampled drums?  I would think that Maniac Mansion utilizes them.</div>
<br />I wasn't aware of that, as I had never played it. In that case we <em>would</em> need the double-clocking protection circuit.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
